sctools_demultiplex - Alignment files barcode-based de-multiplexer.
===================================================================

SYNOPSIS

DESCRIPTION
    sctools_demultiplex is a tool for de-multiplexing alignment BAM or SAM
    files splitting its records indifferent output files, according to the
    barcode of eachalignment record.

REQUIRED ARGUMENTS
    ALIGNMENTS INPUT_FILE
          Path of the SAM or BAM file containing the alignments records to be
          de-multiplexed. Valid filetypes are: .sam[.*] and .bam, where * is
          any of the following extensions: gz and bgzf for transparent
          (de)compression.

OPTIONS
    -h, --help
          Display the help message.
    --version
          Display version information.

  Input/Output options:
    --barcodes-csv INPUT_FILE
          Path to the CSV file storing the barcodes to be de-multiplexed.
          Notice that the barcode value is expected to be found in first
          position.
    -o, --output-directory STRING
          Path of the directory where de-multiplexed files are stored.
          Default: ..
    --alignment-records-batch INTEGER
          Maximum size of the batch of alignment records loaded in main
          memory. Default: 1048576.
    -b, --bed
          Ouput bed files alongside bam ones.

  Filter options:
    --forbidden-tags STRING
          Coma-separated list of tags that are forbidden in any valid
          alignment records. If an alignment record contains any of the tags
          specified here, it is not considered for the purpose of the
          de-multiplexing procedure.
    --min-mapq INTEGER
          Minimum mapping quality any alignment record must have, to be
          considered for the purpose of the de-multiplexing procedure.
          Default: 0.

